CLAUDE.md:
    I have 2 CLAUDE.mds, one for the AI OS itself and another for my second brain 

    Since it is the brain of the systems, keep it concise and kind of deterministic, also smart/versatile and super in providing instructions
    It would wire up the entire ai os system. Integrated with every components old/new. Because all navigations to different components/folders get started with this file.
    It chains everything up and manage the entire thing like a narve system, that's why it is called the brain. 

    It would be quite deterministic about its goal/objectives and how to achieve them.

    evolution:
        After some iterations and judgement based on the generations, with consultancy with admin, the CLAUDE.md can be modified to be more aligned with the project goal. 
        If any new features to get added, then the new thing must be connected like neuron wiring with the CLAUDE.md 
    test:
        since lots of components would be wired up like mcps, skills, commands, hooks, logs, cronjobs, system prompts, documentations, databases, templates and more
        there is a need for testing every components such that every edge cases (hidden test cases) get resolved also, 
        it would make sure the CLAUDE.md is 100% working with the components. 
        
        For the first time building the CLAUDE.md, you would do the entire testing.
        After the first version, you would just test the new things getting added. 